RainbruRPG::Core::TokenizerDbg

RainbruRPG::Core::TokenizerDbg Class Reference

#include <tokenizerdbg.h>

List of all members.

Detailed Description

A class used to debug the Tokenizer return structure.

The tokenizer is used to understand the debugging console commands. To debug the Tokenizer messages, i have used this class.

Member Function Documentation

void RainbruRPG::Core::TokenizerDbg::debug ( tTokentizerReturn  t  ) 

The call of this method will run the debugger on the parameter.

It will print an information message on the standard output and call :

  • debugCmdType()
  • debugTxt()
  • debugErr()

Parameters:
t the tTokentizerReturn structure to debug

void RainbruRPG::Core::TokenizerDbg::debugCmdType ( tTokentizerReturn  t  )  [private]

Debug the command type of a tTokentizerReturn structure.

It will print an information message according to the command type of the parameter :

  • SIMPLE COMMAND;
  • DOUBLE COMMAND;
  • TRIPLE COMMAND;
  • QUAD COMMAND;
  • QUINT COMMAND.

Parameters:
t the tTokentizerReturn structure to debug

void RainbruRPG::Core::TokenizerDbg::debugErr ( tTokentizerReturn  t  )  [private]

Print the error message of a tTokentizerReturn structure.

It will print a message if an error is returned in the tTokentizerReturn structure passed in parameter :

  • The command is empty
  • A quote is missing
  • A bracket is missing
  • An unknown separator (?) is missing
  • No error

Parameters:
t the tTokentizerReturn structure to debug

void RainbruRPG::Core::TokenizerDbg::debugTxt ( tTokentizerReturn  t  )  [private]

Print the values of a tTokentizerReturn structure.

It will print an the values of the folowwing fields :

  • cmd
  • obj
  • att
  • val
  • id
